      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"2. NOVA'S FERN showed blistering pace early and gave a sight when in the minors, beaten 1.75 lengths over 530m Murray Bridge in 30.25. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Rates highly and will give a great sight. 7. BIG DIESEL turned in a plain run last time when fifth at this track over 595m behind Wilma's Our Girl (35.45) in a Grade 6. Was a winner prior to that. Yet to score from this box but has never missed the frame in two starts. Better than last start and can bounce back. 1. VINTAGE FLAIR showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fifth (31.55) in a Grade 5 at this track. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Has ability and can measure up. 6. MEMORIES OF ROSE deserves plenty of thought over this distance.\",\"runners\":[2,7,1,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
